{
  "texts": [
    "As a result, creating sufficient probe and concept datasets is an active research area that has a significant impact on interpretation effectiveness.",
    "Standardized evaluation methodologyAccording to the literature, the evaluation methodology must be standardised in three major ways: 1) Sufficiency Metrics such as Meaningfulness [106,186], Completeness [105,154], Importance [160][161][162]; 2) Experimental parameters such as neural network settings such as layer depth [110,160], Layer width, and target layer [98,146], and 3) test dataset selection [88,164].",
    "For example, as pointed out by [159], Fidelity scores are not always required for intrinsically based interpretation methods like MCD [154], Hierarchical CBM [90], CBM-AUC [89], but they are for post-hoc methods like PCBM [88], DISSECT [162], CAR [160].",
    "Furthermore, the test samples should include both the best and worst cases to demonstrate the model's performance in different scenarios, and they should not be cherrypicked to include only the best samples [53].",
    "However, current studies compared the proposed methods to standard evaluation metrics using different efficiency criteria, so we don't know how close or far they are."
  ]
}